"title": "5894: intelligence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5894",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The natural ability to acquire knowledge and to learn skills. It is not emphasised in Scripture because wisdom is viewed primarily in spiritual and moral terms. Human cleverness proves ultimately futile; nevertheless, believers are called to develop and use their minds to the full in God's service and to dedicate gifts and abilities to him.</p>\n<h2>Wisdom is primarily spiritual and moral</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:10\">PRO 9:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:28\">JOB 28:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:10\">PSA 111:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:13\">JAS 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>The spiritual and moral inadequacy of unaided human intelligence</h2>\n<h3>Unaided human intelligence proves futile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:11\">PSA 94:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:11\">ECC 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:12\">ECC 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:4\">DAN 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:21\">ACT 17:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:20\">1CO 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Human intelligence does not bring knowledge of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:20-1Cor1:21\">1CO 1:20–1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:39-John5:40\">JHN 5:39–5:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:22-Rom1:23\">ROM 1:22–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Human intelligence cannot promote godliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:23\">COL 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:1-1Cor8:2\">1CO 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Reliance on human intelligence brings judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:14\">ISA 29:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:13\">JOB 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:25\">ISA 44:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:19\">1CO 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>Many of the first Christians were not intelligent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:26-1Cor1:31\">1CO 1:26–1:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:13\">ACT 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are to use their minds</h2>\n<h3>The mind to be used in serving God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:30\">MRK 12:30</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:37\">MAT 22:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:27\">LUK 10:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:37\">1CO 7:37</a> <em>The mind is to be used in seeking to discern God's will</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:15-1Cor14:18\">1CO 14:15–14:18</a> <em>The mind is to be used in worship.</em></p>\n<h3>God wants to renew the mind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:23\">EPH 4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:16\">HEB 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a></p>\n<h3>The mind must be correctly focused</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:6\">ROM 8:5–8:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:6-Phil4:7\">PHP 4:6–4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:2\">COL 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of intelligent people</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:3\">1SA 25:3</a> <em>Abigail</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:12\">2CH 2:12</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:4\">DAN 1:4</a> <em>young men from Israel exiled in Babylon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:17\">DAN 1:17</a> <em>Daniel, Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:34\">ACT 5:34</a> <em>Gamaliel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:22\">ACT 7:22</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:6-Acts13:7\">ACT 13:6–13:7</a> <em>Sergius Paulus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:24\">ACT 26:24</a> <em>Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of believers using their minds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:9\">ECC 8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:10\">EZR 7:10</a> <em>Ezra</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:25\">ECC 7:25</a> <em>the Teacher</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:12\">DAN 10:12</a> <em>Daniel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:11\">ACT 17:11</a> <em>the Bereans</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:15\">2TI 2:15</a> <em>Paul's expectation for Timothy</em></p>\n<h2>God uses intelligence dedicated to him</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:46-Gen41:49\">GEN 41:46–41:49</a> <em>God uses Joseph's administrative skill</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:2-Exod31:6\">EXO 31:2–31:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:30-Exod35:35\">EXO 35:30–35:35</a> <em>Craftsmen use artistic expertise</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:13-1Kgs7:14\">1KI 7:13–7:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:13-2Chr2:14\">2CH 2:13–2:14</a> <em>Huram does work in bronze for Solomon's temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:15\">2CH 26:15</a> <em>Skilful men design machines for the defence of Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:13-Dan5:14\">DAN 5:13–5:14</a> <em>Daniel's intelligence aids his witness in the Babylonian court</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:3-Luke1:4\">LUK 1:3–1:4</a> <em>Luke's thorough research owes something to his medical training.</em></p>",
